  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is designed to investigate (1) the effects of task-oriented aerobic exercise
      training on cardiorespiratory fitness, cerebral blood flow, oxygenation, functional
      performance, and physical activity in patients with chronic stroke. (2) the association
      between outcomes
    </textblock>
